The paper focuses on vision-language tasks, which involve both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses different language models and word embeddings, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses retrieval-style tasks and text-to-clip retrieval, which are related to information retrieval, a topic covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
